				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>RW wrote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">Oil was $30 a barrel last year. It should be $35 a barrel with the world wide rise in demand and supply.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />
Why should it be $35 a year?  Just because that is what you want?  With the fuel needs of the US government coupled with the explosive economic growth of China, one would imagine that oil requirements would grow exponentially.  Oil is not only used for gas/diesel requirements but is a source of hydrocarbons for synthetic manufacturing purposes - plastics and the like.  
<br />

<br />
