				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">The real concern here with the US economy is that pre-9/11 interest rates facillitated a 2yr period of 1% interest rates so that the country could convince anyone abroad to buy up US debt so that the government could finance a war and a hefty tax cut.  
<br />

<br />
Greenspan had it right when they started to move rates upwards once the picture began to look brighter.  Only thing is, if another crisis begins to stir now or 6-8 months from now, interest rates will still be at very low levels.  This is disasterous because you cannot reduce rates if they are already at a low level.  All of a sudden you are in a situation where you cannot spur on the economy even if you want to, because rates are already too low and you cannot cut them more to entice investment.  There is no room for another tax cut because now there really isnt anyone around to support going deeper into debt. 
<br />

<br />
Its a perfect storm situation, I just hope that it doesnt come to that.
<br />

<br />
Meletus v1.0
<br />
Retired 65 dr00d</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
