			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Fallonn - I'm glad you've raised a family of armed individuals who can work the fire trucks (someone will have to do it if your house catches fire) and repair the roads and electrical lines downed at a storm and the sewer, and deal with miscreant looters as well.  Sure you do. Uh-huh.  Unless you're head of a very large group with very large assets, that seems a bit of an exaggeration. 
<br />

<br />
 I can only infer you are more than willing to let "the free market" have its way.  Sure, unless you're the victim, right?  Oh, but you are.  Said so yourself.  "Big 2 got there first"?  Gee, I'm sorry you're a victim of the ages and time itself and all those people who have been duped by the big 2.  Yawn.  Totally bogus argument.  Yes, all vested interests like things the way they want, Libertarians included.  If your philosophy had legs, it wouldn't be fairly universally rejected.  That's the free market.  
<br />

<br />
Having explored Libertarianism in Texas for a number of years when younger, I found that it does have some solutions that are very good, but will never get the chance to implement them due to other more extreme views rejected by the vast majority of American society.  But that's not what this thread was about.  It was about oil monopolists, oil policy, and the economic trainwreck coming.
<br />

<br />
It's not ad-hominem to name selfishness.  I have named a behavior you have asserted that concerns the elderly and young.  No, I don't think what you assert about stealing.  Compassion = to be able to put oneself in another's place, among other standard definitions. I also hope you never steal yourself, since you have this thing about being stolen from.  Otherwise your standard is a bit fuzzy.  Oh yeah - sorry you're so touchy about spelling.  You might need a spell check yourself before you post.  Found a few typos on your post, too.  Oh well, we do have to deal with each other's typing, don't we?
<br />

<br />
For the record, don't want or need your dough for my pet causes.  Do believe that in a free society that uses common sources (fire trucks, power lines, sewers, traffic light systems, etc.) we owe something for that.  And I just don't want to turn the infirm and mentally disabled out on the street, a la Reagan.  That's not compassion
<br />

<br />
Funny you also have this thing about body parts.  Is that Libertarian?  Glad you raised so many "neices" - spell check again - and nephews.  I suppose if I asked their parents they'd tell me that you raised them, not their parents.  So either you're fostering dependency, or not telling us the whole truth.  Which is it?
<br />

<br />
Two can play your reasoning game.  I could turn everything you say into a spin, and you could do the same.  Dumb game for a communication, which I'm not sure you can do, with attack after attack.  And you will wind up alone if you're as ugly and insulting with those close to you as you are here.  Shows a distinct lack of class, if nothing else.
<br />

<br />
Shell answered poppa's how did it affect me.  This is not an unsubstantiated opinion.  Check out the price of gas everywhere, and then we can talk about the refiner's concept of supply and demand.  I also agree that government should not interfere in most parts of our lives.  But in any society there are shared resources to be mobilized to the common good.  It's definitely in the common good that transcients can't deficate in the public water supply or you and your self-sufficient bunch would be getting cholera and whining about it at your local hospital as they gouged you for all they could get, a la free markets.  
<br />

<br />
Kerry is a secularist.  Bush is a religionist.  Re: concentration camps, the Nazis were proud of their Christianity.  So were the Fascists in Spain and Italy.  So were Americans as we threw our Japanese-American citizens into camps. Will take secular over religion every time it comes to civil liberties, since the "Big 3" religions currently globally popular all have an imperative to convert you, exile you, or kill you.  Think about it.
<br />

<br />
"What's wrong with anarchy? LOL."  You are surely kidding.  I've been in situations of true social anarchy, and the law of the jungle prevails.  This is not compassion, your own take notwithstanding.  As for health insurance, I don't think there should be any.  That's government propping up an economic monopoly involving a few big boys who get to tell us how much health we can afford, not free market.  Strictly between patient and doctor.  
<br />

<br />
Also feel we should have the right to choose our own cures, not be bound to system of drug company monopolists.  In that situation, in the '30s the AMA bought Congress to guarantee allopathic medicine and drug pushers sole monopoly over health care. For a while homeopaths and naturopaths were illegal, so to speak.  Now they operate under severe legal constraints, mainly due to monopolists having control over gov't policy.  It's not the guv - it's the lobbyists, another aspect of your free market.
<br />

<br />
Some of what your final paragraph states may be true, but eventually human greed takes over.  Friend of mine in the midwest ordered windows for her house recently.  Price spiked a few days later due to hurricanes a thousand miles away creating demand for window materials.  Now she can't afford them.  Her problem, right?
<br />

<br />
Problem with uncontrolled free markets is that those who are born on third base have major advantages getting to home.  And the Yankees would win every year due to having biggest market for the money train.  Once there's any intervention in anyone's right to sell faulty cars, watches, drugs, price gouge, manipulate markets, or do an Enron that screws millions, then you're going to have to appoint someone to oversee that doesn't happen.  Or do you think the Enron gamers should have been allowed to do whatever they wanted?  If so, then you're advocating a system that would eventually crush you under its wheels.  In which case, might as well mail all your money to the Saudis and see how much they care the next time there's a fire in your hood.<br />_________________<br />If not here, where? If not now, when?</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
